   <mads:note type="source">TLG Canon of Greek Authors and Works, Third Edition, pg. 300</mads:note>
   <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 3, 1867, p. 230:
   "Phaedimus, 3, an epigrammatic poet, four of whose epigrams are contained in the Greek Anthology....
   We learn from Stephanus that he was a native of Bisanthe in Macedonia...He also
   perhaps wrote an epic poem entitled Heracleia"</mads:note>
   <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly:  "Phaedimus, Elegist, from Bisanthe in Thrace or, according to others, from Amastri
      ....also composed epigrams; four are preserved in the Anthologia Palatina...Author of a  Ἡρακλεία ( Hērakleía ) of which Ath. 11,498e 
      cites one hexameter ...""Di Marco, Massimo (Fondi Latina).       "Phaedimus." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2009. Brill Online. </mads:note>
